Xi and Putin's strategic friendship
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin arrived in Beijing on Tuesday, on the eve of a major military parade, for what was at least his 45th meeting with Chinese President Xi Jinping since both leaders have held power. Their close ties reflect the alliance Russia and China have forged against the West.

For France's teachers, a back-to-school season marked by growing weariness
description: While they still say they love their profession, teachers expressed growing fatigue in the face of overcrowded classrooms, ever-dwindling resources, and nonstop reforms that leave their jobs uncertain. As a result, many are considering leaving the field altogether.

headline: Block Everything is 'a movement structured almost exclusively around radical left sympathizers'
description: Bristielle conducted a study in the online groups of the Block Everything movement on September 10. He found that only 27% of respondents claimed to have been part of the Yellow Vest movement in 2019, he explained in an interview with Le Monde.

headline: Louvre says 'game over' to its Nintendo 3DS visitor guide
description: Since 2012, visitors to the Paris museum have been able to use Nintendo's handheld console as a multimedia guide. The service ends on Monday, and the consoles will be returned to Nintendo.

headline: Thomas Piketty: 'To succeed in the climate transition, we must redistribute wealth differently'
description: In an interview with Le Monde, the French economist explains that protecting the planet from climate change cannot be achieved without reducing inequality.

headline: The discreet rise of facial recognition around the world
description: Driven by artificial intelligence and backed by some political leaders as well as private companies, this highly sensitive technology is becoming commonplace in many countries and is making inroads across Europe.

headline: Marcel Gauchet, historian and philosopher: 'Progressivism has locked itself into a denial of uncomfortable realities'
